# Awesome Portfolio Template

Next.js 16 + Tailwind CSS v4 + Framer Motion + next-intl (i18n) + next-themes (dark mode).

Users customize by editing config and data files, not component code.

## Architecture

src/config/site.ts — Central config (URL, author, social, nav, sections, SEO)
src/data/*.ts — Content data files (profile, experience, career, credentials, speaking, projects)
src/messages/ko.json, en.json — i18n translation strings
src/components/sections/ — Page section components
src/components/layout/ — Header, Footer, MobileDrawer
src/app/[locale]/page.tsx — Main portfolio page
src/app/globals.css — Tailwind v4 + CSS custom properties
public/profile.png — Profile photo

## Customization

1. Edit src/config/site.ts for site settings (URL, author, social, nav, sections, SEO)
2. Edit src/data/*.ts for content — all text fields have ko and en variants for i18n
3. Edit src/messages/ko.json and en.json for UI strings
4. Replace public/profile.png with your photo

## Conventions

- Tailwind CSS v4: @import "tailwindcss" (NOT @tailwind), NO @apply, utility classes in JSX
- Framer Motion: ALWAYS use m import, NEVER motion — LazyMotion provider is active
- i18n: All user-facing text through useTranslations() or data file ko/en fields
- Dark mode: dark: Tailwind variants, next-themes for system preference + toggle
- TypeScript strict mode, no as any / @ts-ignore
- Use cn() from src/lib/utils.ts for conditional class merging

## Common Tasks

Add section: Create src/components/sections/my-section.tsx, add to page.tsx, update siteConfig.nav + sections, add i18n keys
Add language: Create src/messages/{locale}.json, update src/i18n/routing.ts + middleware.ts, add locale to data fields
Remove section: Set false in siteConfig.sections, remove from siteConfig.nav

## Anti-Patterns

- NEVER use motion (use m for LazyMotion)
- NEVER hardcode site URL or author info (use siteConfig)
- NEVER use @apply in Tailwind v4
- NEVER suppress TypeScript errors (as any, @ts-ignore)
- NEVER skip i18n for user-facing text
- NEVER put content in components (use src/data/)
- NEVER use transition-all (be specific: transition-colors, transition-shadow)

## Commands

npm run dev — Dev server (localhost:3000)
npm run build — Production build
npm run lint — ESLint
